cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object detection and scene classification. The use of latent discriminative learning also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of appearance-based clustering, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of multiple components and scene classification could also suggest that it belongs to the natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories, respectively.
